            <title>[CAMEL-12753] OPTIONS Http request on REST resource returns incorrect content of Allow header</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-12753</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a REST resource which consumes multiple Http methods (for example GET, POST and PUT). If I send OPTIONS request to resource and I expect to receive Allow Http header with this content:&lt;br/&gt;
Allow: GET,POST,PUT,OPTIONS&lt;br/&gt;
That does not happen because I receive header which contains only two methods one of them is OPTIONS.&lt;br/&gt;
Allow: GET,OPTIONS&lt;br/&gt;
I have try multiple implementations and only camel-restlet works as I expect. These components contain bug:&lt;br/&gt;
camel-undertow&lt;br/&gt;
camel-servlet&lt;br/&gt;
camel-jetty&lt;br/&gt;
camel-netty4-http&lt;/p&gt;</description>
